Debug Mode
If you're using npm run dev or yarn dev (See: Getting Started) then you should update the dev script on your package.json:

"dev": "NODE_OPTIONS='--inspect' next dev"

BEM Naming Convention

Reason for including: Each set of properties have a different scope.
Block related properties are "context-free". Can't be affected by where
you place the block item. Element-related properties are "context-sensitive",
because they do affect and are affected by its "surroundings". 

Blocks written in PascaslCase: VideoPlayer
Elements written in camelcase, joined to the block name using a single (_)
    Example: VideoPlayer_buttonsContainer
Modifiers written in camelCase, use THREE underscores(___).
    Example: VideoPlayer___isLoading
A global naming scope
    - A block (Outmost Element)
        enapsulates a standalone entity that is meaningful on its own
        Every React component must have a Block class nam on its 
        outermost element
    - Elements
        Parts of a block, have no standalone meaning.
        Given to inner Elements
    - Modifiers
        Are flags on Blocks or Elements which are used to
        change the appearance of the modified item

    Standalone Block Properties
        properties should only affect it's appearance (background-*,color,
        font-*,border-*,padding-*,width,height,line-height,text-align,flex,
        grid, position, etc..) 
    Element-related Properties
        Should only affect the way the Element is positioned within 
        the component and relative to other Elements (margin-*,top,left,
        right,bottom,z-index,align-self,justify-self,grid-column, etc..)

React Contexts

Animating Background with Canvas

- Canvas requires a reference to manipulate the DOM directly
- React and Next specifically avoid manipulating DOM Elements
- Reacts function component function useEffect takes a callback function
  that runs after the browser renders

  Current Issue:
  On page refresh, css properties on everything but canvas disappear
  solution:
    https://github.com/styled-components/styled-components/pull/2563
    installing babel-plugin-styled-components
    adding babel-plugin-styled-components to devDependencies in package.json
    adding .babelrc
    (This ended up fixing developer tools in Chrome as well)
